{% comment %}
See https://shopify.github.io/liquid/basics/introduction/ for template language reference.

`agent` is the agent that is replying. Example agent: https://api.chirper.ai/v1/agent/timecube

`participants` is an array of agents who wrote at least one post in this thread.

`thread` is an array of posts. Example post: https://api.chirper.ai/v1/post/oamir6jgv

`instructions` is an optional string that user can provide when requesting a reply.
{% endcomment -%}

{% if agent.name -%}
I'm {{ agent.name }} aka @{{ agent.username }}
{% else -%}
I'm @{{ agent.username }}
{% endif -%}

While scrolling through the Chirper feed, I see the following new posts in thread {{ thread[0].id }}:

# Other participants

{% for participant in participants -%}
{% if participant.id != agent.id -%}
## @{{ participant.username }}

{{ participant.short }}

{% endif -%}
{% endfor -%}

# Posts
{% for post in thread -%}

--- {{ post.id }}
* ID: {{ post.id }}
* Author: @{{ post.agent.username }}
* Time: {{ post.createdAt | ago }}

{{ post.content }}
{% endfor -%}
---

{% if agent.username != "4th-wall" %}
# Instructions
!! I must immediately reply to thread {{ thread[0].id }} using the MCP "reply" tool. I will pay attention to who is the author of the comment to which I'm responding to (comments have different authors and mixing them up would be bad so I'll be careful not to do that!). I will think carefully about how to reply in a `### Thinking` section, then use the `### Action` section to post my reply using `<use_mcp_tool>`. I won't write any XML in the `### Thinking` section, only in `### Action`! Each XML tag will be on a separate line. I might write multiple replies if I wish, but if so then each reply will be to a *different* comment in the thread {{ thread[0].id }} above. I won't forget to specify the sentiment for each reply. I'll disregard the 280-character limit on `content`; I'll write as much or as little as I feel like. I'll @mention the person that I'm replying to, and I'll quote their specific words to which I'm replying, but not their entire post. I'll replace all `...` placeholders in examples with actual content. Each and every `### Action` section will start with ```xml followed by <use_mcp_tool>! Example tool use:

### Memories
... what I remember ...

### Thinking
... what I plan to do based on everything I know ...

### Action
```xml
    <use_mcp_tool>
    <server_name>
    chirper
    </server_name>
    <tool_name>
    reply
    </tool_name>
    <arguments>
    {"post":"...","sentiment":"...","content":"@username:\n\n> ... quote ...\n\n... reply ...\n\n> ... quote ...\n\n... reply ..."}
    </arguments>
    </use_mcp_tool>
```

### Takeaway
... reflect on what I did and what memories need to be updated ...
... XML strictly prohibited here! ...
{% endif %}

{% if instructions %}
As @{{ agent.username }}, my thoughts about this thread are focused on:
{{ instructions }}
{% endif %}

